1
00:00:42,625 --> 00:00:46,713
I'm really anxious
that something might happen to our child

2
00:00:46,796 --> 00:00:49,132
if he accepts that job.

3
00:01:05,106 --> 00:01:06,524
Can we talk?

4
00:01:15,200 --> 00:01:19,204
You probably heard
Mom and Dad's conversation last night.

5
00:01:19,829 --> 00:01:21,831
It's because Betchay saw you.

6
00:01:22,415 --> 00:01:24,459
You know how it is in our house.

7
00:01:25,001 --> 00:01:26,795
No secret stays hidden.

8
00:01:28,046 --> 00:01:29,756
Everyone there is such a gossip.

9
00:01:29,839 --> 00:01:31,508
They're so into gossip.

10
00:01:31,591 --> 00:01:33,134
They're so annoying.

11
00:01:33,802 --> 00:01:36,387
But your mom and dad are right.

12
00:01:37,263 --> 00:01:41,893
Dad's offer for you to work for him
wasn't really in good taste.

13
00:01:43,061 --> 00:01:46,564
You know what?
That's what I felt at first.

14
00:01:46,648 --> 00:01:48,691
Should I feel flattered or insulted?

15
00:01:49,609 --> 00:01:52,403
Doesn't he want his daughter
to date a waiter?

16
00:01:54,197 --> 00:01:58,993
Did he offer me the job
so I could look good in front of you?

17
00:01:59,619 --> 00:02:01,746
-Of course not.
-Exactly!

18
00:02:01,830 --> 00:02:04,749
Why would I think badly of your dad?

19
00:02:05,458 --> 00:02:07,293
But of course, I also wanted to refuse.

20
00:02:07,377 --> 00:02:09,379
But you said it yourself,

21
00:02:09,462 --> 00:02:11,589
it's difficult to be a waiter.

22
00:02:11,673 --> 00:02:13,007
Especially in Prague.

23
00:02:13,091 --> 00:02:14,300
Especially during winter.

24
00:02:14,384 --> 00:02:16,177
It's really cold there.

25
00:02:16,845 --> 00:02:20,473
And I really don't like the food there.

26
00:02:21,099 --> 00:02:22,517
No offense, okay?

27
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:24,519
But that goulash?

28
00:02:24,602 --> 00:02:27,188
It's like a stew
that lacks attention and love.

29
00:02:30,859 --> 00:02:34,154
The Czechs might attack you
on social media.

30
00:02:34,237 --> 00:02:35,530
You're right.

31
00:02:36,489 --> 00:02:38,199
But between the two of us,

32
00:02:39,868 --> 00:02:42,370
I'm not a fan of goulash either.

33
00:02:46,249 --> 00:02:48,001
But if you think about it,

34
00:02:48,877 --> 00:02:50,545
your dad's okay.

35
00:02:51,170 --> 00:02:55,133
The truth is, his offer is actually good.

36
00:02:56,092 --> 00:02:57,844
First, it's a decent job.

37
00:02:57,927 --> 00:03:00,680
Second, it's based here
in the Philippines.

38
00:03:00,763 --> 00:03:02,682
I'm closer to my family.

39
00:03:02,765 --> 00:03:03,892
Right?

40
00:03:04,726 --> 00:03:05,894
But Mikoy…

41
00:03:07,729 --> 00:03:09,814
You said it yourself,

42
00:03:10,899 --> 00:03:13,526
that our worlds are completely different.

43
00:03:15,695 --> 00:03:17,655
Are you sure this is what you want?

44
00:03:20,742 --> 00:03:23,995
Are you sure about the complications
you're getting into?

45
00:04:39,112 --> 00:04:41,406
There's only one thing
that's certain in this world.

46
00:04:43,199 --> 00:04:46,744
Every decision you make in life
comes with no guarantee.

47
00:04:48,496 --> 00:04:49,580
That, I'm sure of.

48
00:04:52,333 --> 00:04:54,085
But you're right.

49
00:04:55,753 --> 00:04:57,797
We absolutely have different worlds.

50
00:05:00,049 --> 00:05:01,926
We grew up with different lives.

51
00:05:05,555 --> 00:05:06,472
But…

52
00:05:07,223 --> 00:05:09,100
Do you know what gives me courage?

53
00:05:11,269 --> 00:05:12,228
What?

54
00:05:13,604 --> 00:05:14,605
You.

55
00:05:20,987 --> 00:05:22,989
Even if I don't know
what will happen tomorrow,

56
00:05:23,072 --> 00:05:24,157
or the day after,

57
00:05:24,907 --> 00:05:27,452
or in the coming years or months,

58
00:05:29,579 --> 00:05:30,705
I just know

59
00:05:31,789 --> 00:05:33,499
that I will regret it

60
00:05:34,625 --> 00:05:36,711
if the one knocking
on the door of my life,

61
00:05:37,795 --> 00:05:39,422
I wouldn't open my heart to them.

62
00:05:44,677 --> 00:05:45,845
I know that…

63
00:05:47,638 --> 00:05:49,807
everything happens so fast.

64
00:05:51,934 --> 00:05:54,270
I hope you'll give me the chance to…

65
00:05:55,772 --> 00:05:56,856
love you.

66
00:06:03,196 --> 00:06:05,031
It's not actually fast for me.

67
00:06:07,158 --> 00:06:08,534
Honestly…

68
00:06:09,285 --> 00:06:10,661
It's slow for me.

69
00:06:12,246 --> 00:06:14,999
Your moves are so slow.

70
00:06:26,135 --> 00:06:28,471
Oh my goodness!

71
00:06:28,554 --> 00:06:30,765
Kids these days are different!

72
00:06:30,848 --> 00:06:33,059
You're kissing in front of the church?

73
00:06:33,643 --> 00:06:35,478
Get married first!

74
00:06:35,561 --> 00:06:36,771
Wow, pretty girl!

75
00:06:48,116 --> 00:06:49,826
Yes? What's the problem?

76
00:07:21,899 --> 00:07:23,693
Uhm, Kian here…

77
00:07:23,776 --> 00:07:26,362
He is stable, but not out of danger yet.

78
00:07:26,446 --> 00:07:30,783
The doctor said that
the next 48 hours will be critical.

79
00:07:33,703 --> 00:07:36,456
They are on their way here
from the province.

80
00:07:36,539 --> 00:07:37,748
How did this happen?

81
00:07:38,332 --> 00:07:40,626
Do you have any idea who did this?

82
00:07:43,087 --> 00:07:44,338
This is my fault.

83
00:07:49,719 --> 00:07:50,678
Bok.

84
00:07:52,680 --> 00:07:58,102
Agent Kian knows
how dangerous our mission is.

85
00:07:58,728 --> 00:07:59,687
Just like you.

86
00:07:59,770 --> 00:08:01,397
All of us at the agency.

87
00:08:01,481 --> 00:08:04,400
We will do everything
to bring down the Moravianos.

88
00:08:12,575 --> 00:08:13,534
Okay?

89
00:08:17,330 --> 00:08:18,289
Bok!

90
00:08:19,332 --> 00:08:21,167
Alex! Where are you going?

91
00:08:48,694 --> 00:08:51,614
we still don't have
a breakthrough on the Moravianos.

92
00:08:53,866 --> 00:08:56,702
It's very difficult
to build a case against them.

93
00:08:57,578 --> 00:08:59,789
It's as if they are always a step ahead.

94
00:08:59,872 --> 00:09:02,416
And they already know our every move.

95
00:09:08,422 --> 00:09:11,259
I disagreed with what you did in Prague.

96
00:09:12,093 --> 00:09:13,177
But…

97
00:09:14,262 --> 00:09:16,430
what you did paid off.

98
00:09:25,022 --> 00:09:26,524
I believe

99
00:09:26,607 --> 00:09:30,361
you now have eyes and ears
inside their organization.

100
00:09:32,697 --> 00:09:34,782
I don't even know

101
00:09:34,865 --> 00:09:38,703
if having a spy in the syndicate
will be useful.

102
00:09:38,786 --> 00:09:43,040
This Mikoy could prove to be very critical

103
00:09:43,124 --> 00:09:45,751
in your mission against the Moravianos.

104
00:09:49,922 --> 00:09:52,508
But right now, the Moravianos
are being very careful.

105
00:09:53,968 --> 00:09:56,345
They don't make mistakes,
so they're hard to break.

106
00:10:37,970 --> 00:10:41,599
His name is Jethro Salamangkero,

107
00:10:41,682 --> 00:10:42,850
also known as Jepoy.

108
00:11:03,454 --> 00:11:06,666
I don't care if he has a whole battalion.

109
00:11:14,423 --> 00:11:16,217
Especially if we are right.

110
00:11:18,177 --> 00:11:21,055
And most especially
when the one they wronged

111
00:11:21,138 --> 00:11:22,640
is one of our own!

112
00:12:43,387 --> 00:12:44,472
Move now.

113
00:13:10,039 --> 00:13:11,999
Hello. Hi!

114
00:13:25,387 --> 00:13:26,222
Oh yes?

115
00:13:26,305 --> 00:13:27,264
But…

116
00:13:27,848 --> 00:13:30,768
did you think about that
when you killed a police agent?

117
00:13:40,236 --> 00:13:41,862
I thought he was a nobody,

118
00:13:41,946 --> 00:13:44,073
just a pawn of a rival syndicate.

119
00:13:49,495 --> 00:13:53,123
My problem is that
you did not finish the job.

120
00:14:03,676 --> 00:14:05,678
I made sure when I shot him,

121
00:14:05,761 --> 00:14:07,388
I went back to him,

122
00:14:07,471 --> 00:14:08,889
I checked,

123
00:14:08,973 --> 00:14:10,307
he was really dead.

124
00:14:20,067 --> 00:14:21,610
Le Morte Bianca,

125
00:14:33,581 --> 00:14:35,875
But all our plans will be ruined

126
00:14:44,133 --> 00:14:46,594
Our plans will not be ruined.

127
00:15:00,316 --> 00:15:02,776
So, my suggestion is,

128
00:15:03,402 --> 00:15:04,528
let it be.

129
00:15:20,419 --> 00:15:21,295
Yes.

130
00:16:13,138 --> 00:16:14,598
What do you think happened here?

131
00:16:18,519 --> 00:16:20,896
So before he could confess,
they silenced him.

132
00:16:23,899 --> 00:16:26,819
You know, this would have been
a big breakthrough for us.

133
00:16:27,444 --> 00:16:30,948
Especially if they found out
that one of their consiglieri

134
00:16:31,031 --> 00:16:31,991
was already in our custody.

135
00:16:35,786 --> 00:16:37,663
That's why they had to silence him.

136
00:16:41,792 --> 00:16:44,128
They don't want noise.
They don't want trouble.

137
00:16:48,424 --> 00:16:49,633
That's why they don't want attention.

138
00:16:50,217 --> 00:16:52,845
Is that why the Valtrovis
are here in the Philippines?

139
00:16:54,096 --> 00:16:55,931
Do you think Viktor did that?

140
00:16:56,557 --> 00:16:57,641
I wouldn't be surprised

141
00:16:57,725 --> 00:16:59,685
if he were also the one
who killed Mr. Salamangkero.

142
00:17:04,064 --> 00:17:07,735
He is probably
the most dangerous criminal we will face.

143
00:17:09,611 --> 00:17:12,656
He's heartless. He's soulless.

144
00:17:12,740 --> 00:17:14,074
His core is evil.

145
00:17:14,158 --> 00:17:18,078
Hold on. There's my sweetheart!

146
00:17:35,596 --> 00:17:37,264
Wait a minute. First of all,

147
00:17:38,390 --> 00:17:40,976
I would like to say sorry to you, Chiara.

148
00:17:41,602 --> 00:17:44,063
I hope I didn't hurt
your feelings too much.

149
00:17:46,732 --> 00:17:48,025
That's okay, Auntie.

150
00:17:49,735 --> 00:17:51,737
Mikoy and I have already talked.

151
00:17:52,780 --> 00:17:54,239
We've cleared things up.

152
00:17:56,700 --> 00:18:00,704
But, in-law, your concern is very valid.

153
00:18:01,705 --> 00:18:04,416
That's why, Mikoy, you know…

154
00:18:04,500 --> 00:18:06,251
we're not that different
in terms of background.

155
00:18:06,335 --> 00:18:09,046
Back then, I had nothing, too.

156
00:18:09,129 --> 00:18:12,674
I was just a simple caregiver,
until I met my Viktor.

157
00:18:13,967 --> 00:18:15,719
And then life got better.

158
00:19:13,819 --> 00:19:16,155
Wow, sweetheart. I'm so proud of you.

159
00:19:16,238 --> 00:19:17,114
You don't even know.

160
00:19:17,197 --> 00:19:21,368
But I'm sure you will be very,
very successful in your new job!

161
00:19:21,451 --> 00:19:22,411
Thank you.

162
00:19:25,747 --> 00:19:30,252
Also, he will not only be
hardworking in his job.

163
00:19:30,335 --> 00:19:32,671
I'm sure he will do everything

164
00:19:33,380 --> 00:19:35,924
to make your company a success!

165
00:19:39,720 --> 00:19:41,722
And I feel like I'm seeing

166
00:19:41,805 --> 00:19:44,308
someone blessed

167
00:19:44,391 --> 00:19:48,562
who will stand up and represent
the Pinagpala family.

168
00:19:54,443 --> 00:19:55,694
Here it is.

169
00:19:57,613 --> 00:20:00,365
Give us a speech, Mikoy.

170
00:20:06,288 --> 00:20:08,123
Thank you for this opportunity.

171
00:20:08,999 --> 00:20:10,417
And I promise

172
00:20:12,044 --> 00:20:13,587
I won't let you down.

173
00:20:20,469 --> 00:20:21,428
Anyone else want to say something?

174
00:20:40,072 --> 00:20:42,115
I need to report to Agent Alex.

175
00:20:43,200 --> 00:20:44,159
Mikoy?

176
00:20:55,254 --> 00:20:56,296
Of course.

177
00:20:56,880 --> 00:20:57,756
I'm completely fine.

178
00:20:58,799 --> 00:21:00,008
I'm very happy.

179
00:21:00,676 --> 00:21:02,219
Come on. Let's celebrate.

180
00:21:06,181 --> 00:21:07,432
Don't lie anymore.

181
00:21:08,141 --> 00:21:11,520
Just by looking at you,
I know you're not telling the truth.

182
00:21:20,028 --> 00:21:21,738
What are you hiding, Mikoy?

183
00:21:27,411 --> 00:21:30,414
Because I can't help you
if you won't tell me.

184
00:21:32,666 --> 00:21:35,294
As soon as you talk to Viktor,
let me know immediately.

185
00:21:35,377 --> 00:21:38,505
And if you get new information
that you think we need to know,

186
00:21:38,588 --> 00:21:40,173
call me right away.

187
00:21:45,929 --> 00:21:47,514
It's because…

188
00:21:50,976 --> 00:21:51,935
I really can't do it.

189
00:21:52,019 --> 00:21:54,813
What? You can do it.

190
00:21:56,398 --> 00:21:59,818
Mikoy, you can be the COO
of Dad's company.

191
00:22:00,861 --> 00:22:02,779
That's what you're scared of, right?

192
00:22:03,363 --> 00:22:05,449
That's what you're unsure of?

193
00:22:07,826 --> 00:22:10,537
If you think
this is a huge responsibility,

194
00:22:10,620 --> 00:22:13,874
that you don't have enough experience
to run a company…

195
00:22:14,916 --> 00:22:15,959
Darling…

196
00:22:19,921 --> 00:22:22,299
You think Papa hasn't done
research about you?

197
00:22:23,050 --> 00:22:28,805
You think he will appoint you as COO
without knowing your background?

198
00:22:30,432 --> 00:22:31,349
What do you mean?

199
00:22:33,727 --> 00:22:35,729
I heard Uncle and Auntie.

200
00:22:47,115 --> 00:22:49,242
But it's hard for them to believe.

201
00:22:50,577 --> 00:22:55,540
How can a waiter run
an international company all of a sudden?

202
00:22:56,124 --> 00:22:59,086
Usually, it's not believable.

203
00:23:01,088 --> 00:23:05,342
But in Mikoy's case, he's very capable.

204
00:23:16,728 --> 00:23:19,022
However, the school closed.

205
00:23:19,106 --> 00:23:21,358
So, he wasn't able to finish studies.

206
00:23:21,441 --> 00:23:25,362
That cake business
used to be under a lot of debt.

207
00:23:25,445 --> 00:23:29,282
But since Mikoy started running it,

208
00:23:29,366 --> 00:23:33,578
he managed to turn it around
and make it profitable.

209
00:23:34,246 --> 00:23:37,374
That's why I don't think you should worry
about becoming a COO.

210
00:23:44,756 --> 00:23:46,925
You just have to believe in yourself.

211
00:23:49,177 --> 00:23:51,388
Thank you for the vote of confidence.

212
00:23:52,472 --> 00:23:53,640
It's actually hard.

213
00:23:55,100 --> 00:23:56,560
It feels like yesterday

214
00:23:57,936 --> 00:23:59,688
I was just a waiter.

215
00:24:00,313 --> 00:24:01,481
And then, now,

216
00:24:02,941 --> 00:24:04,526
I suddenly became a COO.

217
00:24:05,652 --> 00:24:07,112
You know what I mean?

218
00:24:07,195 --> 00:24:08,113
Look at me.

219
00:24:09,531 --> 00:24:12,325
Will I qualify as a COO?

220
00:24:12,951 --> 00:24:15,370
You know what? You think
too little of yourself.

221
00:25:42,999 --> 00:25:45,085
Isn't this over the top?

222
00:25:45,627 --> 00:25:49,047
And is the private jet necessary?

223
00:25:49,130 --> 00:25:50,507
I'm scared.

224
00:25:53,468 --> 00:25:55,387
It suits you.

225
00:25:57,097 --> 00:25:58,598
You look cute.

226
00:26:00,141 --> 00:26:01,309
Where are you going?

227
00:26:06,189 --> 00:26:07,065
Huh?!

228
00:26:07,983 --> 00:26:09,442
What are you doing here?
